4777.description: A pungent bulb vegetable native to the Near East.

4778.name: Coerthan Carrot
4778.description: A long orange root vegetable commonly grown in the rocky alpine soil of the Coerthas region.

4779.name: Ogre Pumpkin
4779.description: A bright-orange squash which sweetens in flavor when cooked.

4780.name: Ruby Tomato
4780.description: Though many botanists claim this tangy blood red specimen is more closely related to a fruit than a vegetable, it is widely accepted across Eorzea as the latter.

4781.name: Alpine Parsnip
4781.description: A long white root vegetable indigenous to the mountainous region of Coerthas.

4782.name: La Noscean Lettuce
4782.description: A crisp leafy vegetable native to the plains of La Noscea.

4783.name: Cieldalaes Spinach
4783.description: An iron-rich leafy vegetable native to the Cieldalaes.

4784.name: Highland Parsley
4784.description: Oft used as a garnish in other dishes, this pungent vegetable grows in abundance in the mountainous region of upper La Noscea.

4785.name: Paprika
4785.description: A pepper which can be dried and ground to make a mild red spice. It is often used in medicines, as well as in cooking.

4786.name: Nopales
4786.description: An edible oval-leaved cactus brought back by explorers of the New World.

4787.name: Popoto
4787.description: A starchy tuberous vegetable originally introduced to Eorzea by explorers from the distant western continent.

4788.name: Wizard Eggplant
4788.description: A firm purple-skinned vegetable indigenous to the mountains of the Near East. A common wives' tale claims if you eat too many of this vegetable, you will turn into one.

4789.name: Midland Cabbage
4789.description: A round leafy vegetable which prefers the steady climate of the Black Shroud.

4790.name: Aloe
4790.description: A thick spiny-leaved cactus indigenous to the southern continent of Meracydia. The Miqo'te are known to treat severe burns with the cool gel-like substance found inside the leaves.

4791.name: Salt Leek
4791.description: A long, pungent, leafy vegetable that lacks a bulb like that of its cousin, the onion.

4792.name: Ramhorn Zucchini
4792.description: This long, thin variety of squash earns its name from its resemblance to the horn of a mountain ram.

4793.name: Maiden Artichoke
4793.description: The leaf-like bud of an artichoke plant. Due to the roughness of its petals, only the fleshy lower portions can be consumed, as well as the center of the bud, commonly known as the “heart.”

4795.name: Chanterelle
4795.description: An edible mushroom known for its leaf-like appearance as well as its fruit-like fragrance.

4796.name: Gil Bun
4796.description: This tiny round mushroom has a cap which resembles a coin, and is known for its rich flavor and pungent aroma.

4797.name: Button Mushroom
4797.description: A small white mushroom commonly found in moist areas across Eorzea.

4798.name: White Truffle
4798.description: A rare white mushroom that grows in the soil, rather than above it, making the specimen almost impossible to locate. It is treasured as a delicacy for its unique aroma.

4800.name: Black Truffle
4800.description: A rare black mushroom that grows in the soil, rather than above it, making the specimen almost impossible to locate. It is treasured as a delicacy for its unique aroma.

4803.name: Kukuru Bean
4803.description: This seed of the kukuru tree is the primary ingredient in chocolate.

4804.name: Cinderfoot Olive
4804.description: The seed of an olive tree, often preserved in brine or pressed to make oil.

4805.name: Gridanian Chestnut
4805.description: The seed of a chestnut tree, this savory nut is covered in a coat of prickly spikes.

4806.name: Gridanian Walnut
4806.description: The seed of a walnut tree, this fragrant nut is covered by a thin, fleshy outer shell and a hard inner shell.

4807.name: Iron Acorn
4807.description: The seed of an oak tree, this small nut is covered by an extremely hard outer shell.

4808.name: Lowland Grapes
4808.description:
A semisweet variety of grape which has adapted to the volcanic soil abundant on Vylbrand.

A tart fruit commonly grown in mountain orchards in the Coerthas region.

4813.name: Alligator Pear
4813.description:
A soft green fruit, also known as “Shroud butter.” Though not thought to be indigenous to Eorzea, it is not certain how the plant first came to the realm.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m

4814.name: Blood Currants

A tart red berry found growing throughout the Black Shroud.

4815.name: Rolanberry
4815.description:
A tart fruit─one of few still found growing in the devastated region of Mor Dhona.

4816.description:

4818.name: Buffalo Beans
4818.description: A common variety of green bean recognizable by its long thin pods. Buffalo are said to be fond of the beans, and have been known to eat entire crops if left unchecked.

4819.name: Sticky Rice
4819.description: This grain is imported from a land far to the east. When cooked, it has a consistency slightly more glutinous than normal rice.

4820.name: Lalafellin Lentil
4820.description: Thin round beans resembling tiny convex lenses. Thought to have been introduced to Eorzea by the realm's first Lalafellin settlers.

4821.name: Millioncorn
4821.description: Hundreds of sweet yellow kernels adorn each cob of this vegetable native to the recently discovered New World.

4822.name: Jade Peas
4822.description: Sweet green beans recognizable by their thin, crescent-shaped pods.

4823.name: Rye
4823.description: A dark variety of rye grass commonly found growing in the higher elevations of Mor Dhona and Coerthas.

4824.name: Sunset Wheat
4824.description: A common variety of golden-brown wheat eaten as a staple in many of Eorzea's city–states.

4828.name: Cinnamon
4828.description: The sweet-smelling bark of the cinnamon tree is often dried and ground into a spice used to add flavor to confectionaries, though it is also commonly used in medicines.

4829.name: Garlean Garlic
4829.description: A pungent spice used to flavor many different varieties of dishes. It is also thought to ward off vampiric bats, but there is no evidence to substantiate that claim.

4830.name: Black Pepper
4830.description: An aromatic spice used in cooking as well as pickling.

4831.name: Cloves
4831.description: A sweet-smelling spice made from the dried buds of the clove tree. It is used to flavor confectionaries, and as an essential oil.

4832.name: Marjoram
4832.description: A sweet-smelling herb used in cooking and in medicines.

4833.name: Vanilla Beans
4833.description: A sweet-smelling spice made from the dried pod of the rare vanilla plant. It is often used in the making confectionaries as well as medicines.

4834.name: Galago Mint
4834.description: A leafy herb with a crisp, fragrant aroma. It is often used in cooking and in teas, as well as for its essential oil.

4835.name: Ala Mhigan Mustard
4835.description: When dried and ground into a fine powder, this yellow-tinged spice can add quite the kick to any dish.

4836.name: Pearl Ginger
4836.description: An exotic root vegetable native to the Far East that is often dried, ground, and used in cooking as well as in the creation of medicines.

4837.name: Midland Basil
4837.description: A fragrant herb used to flavor various meat and poultry dishes.

4838.name: Dragon Pepper
4838.description: A red-hot spice known to cause severe burns in the mouths of those who consume too many.

4839.name: Laurel
4839.description: A savory spice made from the dried leaves of the laurel bush, or as it is known by some, the yanny bush.

4840.name: Mugwort
4840.description: The young leaves of the mugwort plant are used not only as a spice in cooking, but also as a curative agent in various unguents.

4841.name: Thyme
4841.description: A fragrant herb used to flavor various meat and poultry dishes.

4842.name: Almonds
4842.description: A tear-shaped nut which can be used to season exotic sweets, or pressed for its fragrant oil.

4843.name: Desert Saffron
4843.description: This spice made from the dried styles of the desert saffron flower gives a bright-yellow color to dishes.

4844.name: Nutmeg
4844.description: A sweet-smelling seed that is ground into a powder and used to flavor pastries and tea. It is also widely used in Far Eastern medicines.

4845.name: Sagolii Sage
4845.description: A savory herb often found growing in parched desert environments. It is used in cooking and various medicinal ointments and unguents.

4846.name: Thanalan Tea Leaves
4846.description: These leaves, when dried and steeped in hot water, create a sweet-smelling tea known for its curative properties.

4847.name: Table Salt
4847.description: Finely ground salt used not only for flavoring foods, but for pickling and preserving as well.

4860.name: Dark Vinegar
4860.description: A high-quality distilled vinegar made from select lowland grapes.

4893.name: Hammerhead Shark
4893.description:
A ravenous shark with a hammer-shaped head it uses to quickly detect its prey. This wavekin is most commonly found living in small schools in the Strait of Merlthor.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 3 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on large canvases.]

fish.guide: A ravenous shark with a hammer-shaped head it uses to quickly detect its prey. This wavekin is most commonly found living in small schools in the Strait of Merlthor, but there have been recent reports of schools containing more than five score of the creatures.

4903.name: Silver Shark
4903.description:
A large, spindle-shaped shark commonly found in the Sea of Ash and known to attack without provocation.

[Suitable for display in aquariums tier 4 and higher.]
[Suitable for printing on extra large canvases.]

fish.guide: A large, spindle-shaped shark commonly found in the Sea of Ash and known to attack much larger prey─such as fishers and sailors─without provocation.

5054.name: Dart Frog
5054.description: This tiny frog found in the swamps and lakes of the Black Shroud secretes a powerful poison known to induce paralysis.

5055.name: Lava Toad
5055.description: This giant red toad, native to the swamps of Vylbrand but now found throughout Aldenard, earns its name from the red firerock which once spewed forth from the now-dormant volcano, O'Ghomoro.

8155.description: A crystallized mass of residual spiritbond energies transferred to an article of weaponry or armor by its exceptionally skilled maker during the crafting process.

8785.name: Syrcus Tower
8785.description:
An expertly crafted representation of the ancient crystalline tower.

※One per estate only.

8835.name: Ice Chandelier
8835.description: A breathtaking ceiling fixture crafted using tears taken from the Lady of Frost herself.

8836.name: Diamond Chandelier
8836.description: An awe-inspiring ceiling fixture crafted using tears taken from the Lady of Frost herself and imbued with magicks ancient and forbidden.

9358.name: Wootz Ingot
9358.description: An ingot of smelted wootz alloy.

9359.name: Platinum Nugget
9359.description: A small nugget of impure platinum.

9361.name: Kirimu Leather
9361.description: A large piece of cured skin from the chimerical monstrosity Kirimu.

9363.name: Allagan Wootz Nugget
9363.description: A small chunk of the alloy used by the Allagan Empire to craft heavy armor.

9364.name: Allagan Leather
9364.description: A large piece of treated chimerical leather used by the Allagan Empire to craft light armor.

9366.name: Borax
9366.description: This soft lusterless crystal is believed to stay the hands of corruption and is used in the preservation of organics.

9368.name: Wootz Ore
9368.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing naturally occurring wootz alloy.

9369.name: Raziqsap
9369.description: Developed by a Far Eastern alchemist, this powder is used to harden platinum.

9370.name: Dubbin
9370.description: A greasy mixture of wax, oil, and tallow used for waterproofing and softening leather, while helping maintain its luster.

9373.name: Enchanted Platinum Ink
9373.description: Ink fortified with platinum sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

9376.name: Allagan Catalyst
9376.description: Dubbed a “god in the machina” by those who first discovered it, modern scholars have yet to discover not only what the catalytic agent contains, but exactly how it functions, understanding only that the substance is required to strengthen the properties of certain materials.

9377.name: Ice Tear
9377.description: A glass-like shard retrieved from the fallen Lady of Frost.

9378.name: Diamond Tear
9378.description: A glass-like shard retrieved from the fallen Lady of Frost. It pulses with uncontrollably powerful ice-aspected energies.

9379.name: Syrcus Shard
9379.description: A remarkably transparent piece of Syrcus Tower's outer wall.

9466.name: Level 6 Aetherial Wheel Stand
9466.description:
A metal stand upon which aetherial wheels are placed and spun to charge. Holds three grade 1, two grade 2, and one grade 3 wheel.
※One stand per estate only.

9518.name: Cypress Log
9518.description: A rough-cut log of cypress timber.

9519.name: Pumice
9519.description: Volcanic rock riddled with countless tiny holes which make the stone remarkably lighter than it appears. Parchment makers rub the pieces on vellum to prepare the pages for receiving ink.

9718.name: Longcase Chronometer
9718.description: A precision instrument for telling time. Its towering silhouette adds a touch of gravitas to the ambience of any room.

9730.name: Oriental Altar
9730.description: A miniature wooden altar hung in Doman houses, allowing people to worship the gods within the privacy of their own homes.

9740.name: Oriental Striking Dummy
9740.description:
A striking dummy designed in the Doman fashion.

※Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

9768.name: Tatami Flooring
9768.description: Woven from sweet-smelling rush grass, tatami flooring is the perfect complement to any home furnished in the Doman fashion.

10086.name: Tinker's Calm
10086.description: A tonic commonly used by Disciples of the Hand to increase focus, allowing for enhanced results when deconstructing complex creations.

10092.name: Black Limestone
10092.description: When polished, this rare form of limestone closely resembles marble.

10093.name: Virgin Basilisk Egg
10093.description: While all eggs a basilisk lays contain traces of rare ore, the first egg laid in life is thought to contain the highest concentration, making it highly sought after by potion mixers and alchemists.

10094.name: Little Worm
10094.description: While commonly used as bait by fishers across the realm, little worms also make fine chocobo feed, providing a good source of protein for growing birds.

10095.name: Gregarious Worm
10095.description: A rare form of earthworm, these fat invertebrates also make fine chocobo feed, providing an excellent source of protein for growing birds.

10096.name: Rosemary
10096.description: A savory herb treasured for its ability to enhance focus and concentration.

10097.name: Yafaem Wildgrass
10097.description: After gysahl greens, there's no other verdure a race chocobo would rather sink its beak into.

10098.name: Mazlaya Greens
10098.description: Once found growing all across the island of Mazlaya, this bright-green plant was almost completely wiped out when chocobos brought to the island by farmers devoured nearly every one they could find.

10099.name: Unaspected Crystal
10099.description: For reasons unknown to you, this crystal has completely lost its elemental charge.

10161.name: Tatanora-type Hull
10161.description: Named after the “father” of propeller-powered airships, the design used in this hull is certain to invoke a sense of inspiring nostalgia.

10167.name: Tatanora-type Propellers
10167.description: Taking inspiration from the aether-manipulating flying fish found in the Sea of Clouds, these radical new propellers have been treated with wind-aspected crystals, allowing for increased lift.

10173.name: Tatanora-type Forecastle
10173.description: The front half of a Tatanora-type airship, including the main deck, bowsprit, and banks for extra propellers.

10179.name: Tatanora-type Aftcastle
10179.description: The rear half of a Tatanora-type airship, including the quarter and poop decks, tiller, rudder, ceruleum engine, and tailplane for improved maneuverability.

10335.name: Dark Matter Cluster
10335.description: This substance of unknown origin has the faculty to assimilate with other forms of matter, effectively restoring them to their original condition. Pieces this large are quite rare.

10349.name: Magnificent Mogdelier
10349.description: Marvelously majestic lighting worthy of a moogle king.

10350.name: Hive Ceiling Fan
10350.description:
A ceiling-mounted fan created with the wings of the Gnathic primal Ravana.

※One per estate only.

10351.name: Deep Hive Ceiling Fan
10351.description:
A ceiling-mounted fan created with the wings of the Gnathic primal Ravana. It literally hums with the Lord of the Hive's untamed power.

※One per estate only.

10674.name: Adamantite Helm of Fending
10674.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10675.name: Adamantite Circlet of Fending
10675.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10681.name: Adamantite Armor of Fending
10681.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10682.name: Adamantite Lorica of Fending
10682.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10688.name: Adamantite Gauntlets of Fending
10688.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10689.name: Heavy Adamantite Gauntlets of Fending
10689.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10695.name: Adamantite Tassets of Fending
10695.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10696.name: Adamantite Plate Belt of Fending
10696.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10697.name: Griffin Leather Twinbelt of Fending
10697.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10702.name: Adamantite Chain Hose of Fending
10702.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10703.name: Chimerical Felt Breeches of Fending
10703.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10709.name: Adamantite Sabatons of Fending
10709.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

10710.name: Adamantite Greaves of Fending
10710.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

12083.name: Hive Barding
12083.description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Ravana, the Lord of the Hive.

12104.name: Gordian Bureau
12104.description:
A writing desk crafted from gears found inside the right arm of the mechanical fortress Alexander.

※One per estate only.

12105.name: Savage Gordian Bureau
12105.description:
A writing desk crafted from gears found inside the right arm of the mechanical fortress Alexander. Magicks imbued within the furnishing cause the bureau to emit a soft glow that, while no one can see, all believe is there.

※One per estate only.

12106.name: Gordian Chair
12106.description:
A chair crafted from gears found within the right arm of the mechanical fortress Alexander.

※One per estate only.

12107.name: Savage Gordian Chair
12107.description:
A chair crafted from gears found within the right arm of the mechanical fortress Alexander. Magicks imbued within the furnishing have been known to stimulate the backsides of those who sit on it for any extended period of time.

※One per estate only.

12108.name: Star Sapphire Music Box
12108.description: This expertly crafted music box plays only one half of a melody. Pair with a star ruby music box to complete the song.

12109.name: Star Ruby Music Box
12109.description: This expertly crafted music box plays only one half of a melody. Pair with a star sapphire music box to complete the song.

12111.name: Expanse Fountain
12111.description:
An outdoor fountain created from the baleen of Bismarck, Lord of the Mists.

※One per estate only.

12112.name: Boundless Expanse Fountain
12112.description:
An outdoor fountain practically pulsing with magicks created from the baleen of Bismarck, Lord of the Mists.

※One per estate only.

12220.name: Red Moko Grass
12220.description: A less-common variety of moko grass found growing predominantly in the northern mountainous regions of Aldenard.

12221.name: Cassia Log
12221.description: A rough-cut log of cassia timber. The sweet scent of its bark invokes memories of sweet buns and apple pie.

12222.name: Chemically Treated Chimera Hide
12222.description: The durability of this chimera hide has been enhanced using aetherochemical compounds formulated thousands of summers ago in an Allagan laboratorium.

12223.name: Raw Celestine
12223.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be celestine─a light-blue crystal that is often added to alloys.

12224.name: Vivianite
12224.description: A smoke-blue iron-rich ore often found growing within the fossilized bones of long-dead wavekin.

12230.name: Deep-blue Cluster
12230.description: A vividly colored cluster of crystals aspected to multiple elements.

12231.name: Farreach Canvas
12231.description: Originally conceived by inhabitants of the sparsely settled Farreach to withstand the gale-force winds ceaselessly blowing on the Bloodbrine Sea, this rugged sailcloth is one of few materials suited to air travel.

12232.name: Cassia Lumber
12232.description: Processed cassia lumber. Even with its bark removed, the wood still harbors a faint sweet scent.

12233.name: High Allagan Chimera Leather
12233.description: A large piece of specially treated chimerical leather used by the Allagan Empire to craft high armor.

12254.name: Gordian Gear
12254.description: A round cog removed from Alexander's Gordias sector.

12255.name: Large Gordian Gear
12255.description: A large round cog removed from Alexander's Gordias sector.

12256.name: Bismarck's Baleen
12256.description: Pulled from the Lord of the Mists's massive maw, this thick piece of keratinized tissue appears aspected to both wind and water.

12257.name: Expanse Baleen
12257.description: Pulled from the Lord of the Mists's massive maw, this thick piece of keratinized tissue bristles with the power of the endless skies.

12258.name: Ravana's Forewing
12258.description: Plucked from the Lord of the Hive's back, this remarkably light wing is impossible to tear despite its thinness.

12259.name: Hive Forewing
12259.description: Plucked from the Lord of the Hive's back, this remarkably light wing pulses with uncontrollably powerful aetherial energies.

12518.name: Mythrite Nugget
12518.description: A small nugget of impure mythrite.

12520.name: Hardsilver Nugget
12520.description: A small nugget of impure hardsilver.

12522.name: Aurum Regis Nugget
12522.description: A small nugget of impure aurum regis.

12523.name: Aurum Regis Ingot
12523.description: An ingot of smelted aurum regis.

12524.name: Titanium Nugget
12524.description: A small nugget of impure titanium.

12526.name: Adamantite Nugget
12526.description: A small nugget of impure adamantite.

12528.name: Mythrite Rivets
12528.description: Short mythrite pins with large heads. Used in connecting metal plates.

12529.name: Titanium Rivets
12529.description: Short titanium pins with large heads. Used in connecting metal plates.

12530.name: Adamantite Rivets
12530.description: Short adamantite pins with large heads. Used in connecting metal plates.

12531.name: Mythrite Sand
12531.description: Glowing sand consisting of tiny grains of mythrite.

12532.name: Hardsilver Sand
12532.description: Oily sand containing tiny grains of hardsilver.

12533.name: Aurum Regis Sand
12533.description: Violet sand containing tiny grains of aurum regis.

12534.name: Mythrite Ore
12534.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the rare metal mythrite.

12535.name: Hardsilver Ore
12535.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the rare alchemic metal hardsilver.

12536.name: Aurum Regis Ore
12536.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the rare metal aurum regis.

12537.name: Titanium Ore
12537.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the rare metal titanium.

12538.name: Adamantite Ore
12538.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the rare metal adamantite.

12539.name: Cloud Mica
12539.description: A decent-sized chunk of rock made up of what appears to be thousands of thin sheets of silver crystal compacted together into a single mass.

12540.name: Sun Mica
12540.description: A decent-sized chunk of rock made up of what appears to be thousands of thin sheets of golden crystal compacted together into a single mass.

12542.name: Tiger's Eye
12542.description: A golden-brown jewel consisting of many colored layers. When polished, it resembles the eye of a tiger─a legendary beast believed to be the ancestor of the coeurl.

12544.name: Star Ruby
12544.description: A red jewel that has been shaped and polished instead of faceted, creating the illusion of a six-pointed star within the stone.

12545.name: Star Sapphire
12545.description: A blue jewel that has been shaped and polished instead of faceted, creating the illusion of a six-pointed star within the stone.

12546.name: Opal
12546.description: A milky white jewel that, depending on the angle at which it is held, will exhibit a rainbow of color within the stone.

12550.name: Carnelian
12550.description: A translucent red jewel. Its relative softness makes it easy to carve, and it has been used by royalty throughout history for signet rings.

12551.name: Raw Larimar
12551.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be larimar.

12552.name: Raw Tiger's Eye
12552.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be tiger's eye.

12553.name: Raw Agate
12553.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be agate.

12554.name: Raw Star Ruby
12554.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be star ruby.

12555.name: Raw Star Sapphire
12555.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be star sapphire.

12556.name: Raw Opal
12556.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be opal.

12557.name: Raw Citrine
12557.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be citrine.

12558.name: Raw Chrysolite
12558.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be chrysolite.

12559.name: Raw Mormorion
12559.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be mormorion.

12560.name: Raw Carnelian
12560.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be carnelian.

12561.name: Cloud Mica Whetstone
12561.description: A whetstone carved from cloud mica. Used for sharpening metal or stone blades.

12562.name: Archaeornis Leather
12562.description: A large piece of cured archaeornis skin.

12564.name: Dhalmel Leather
12564.description: A large piece of cured dhalmel hide.

12565.name: Dragon Leather
12565.description: A large piece of cured dragon skin.

12566.name: Amphiptere Leather
12566.description: A large piece of cured amphiptere skin.

12567.name: Griffin Leather
12567.description: A large piece of cured griffin hide.

12568.name: Archaeornis Skin
12568.description: The tough hide of an archaeornis.

12570.name: Dhalmel Hide
12570.description: The smooth hide of a dhalmel.

12571.name: Dragon Skin
12571.description: The thick scaly hide of a dragon.

12572.name: Amphiptere Skin
12572.description: The slick glossy hide of an amphiptere.

12573.name: Griffin Hide
12573.description: The leonine hide of a griffin.

12577.name: Griffin Talon
12577.description: The sharp curved talon of a griffin.

12578.name: Dark Chestnut Log
12578.description: A rough-cut log of dark chestnut timber.

12579.name: Birch Log
12579.description: A rough-cut log of birch lumber.

12582.name: Hallowed Chestnut Lumber
12582.description: Processed dark chestnut lumber purified with hallowed water.

12584.name: Astral Birch Lumber
12584.description: Processed birch lumber treated so that its elemental aspect tips towards astral.

12585.name: Dark Chestnut Branch
12585.description: The thick branch of a dark chestnut tree.

12586.name: Birch Branch
12586.description: The thin branch of a birch tree.

12587.name: Wattle Bark
12587.description: This bark, when boiled down, produces large amounts of tannin─a substance used by leatherworkers to tan hides.

12588.name: Rainbow Cloth
12588.description: Several yalms of undyed rainbow cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

12589.name: Holy Rainbow Cloth
12589.description: Several yalms of rainbow cloth purified with holy water and wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

12590.name: Ramie Cloth
12590.description: Several yalms of undyed ramie cloth wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

12591.name: Hallowed Ramie Cloth
12591.description: Several yalms of ramie cloth purified with holy water and wrapped around a short wooden distaff.

12592.name: Chimerical Felt
12592.description: Several yalms of soft undyed felt created by matting down several layers of hair taken from chimera manes.

12593.name: Astral Silk
12593.description: Several yalms of silk treated so that its elemental aspect would tip slightly towards astral.

12594.name: Rainbow Thread
12594.description: Multicolored yarn spun from rainbow cotton.

12595.name: Ramie Thread
12595.description: Strong, absorbent yarn spun from ramie.

12596.name: Crawler Silk
12596.description: Silk gathered from crawler cocoons and spun into a thin lustrous thread.

12597.name: Rainbow Cotton Boll
12597.description: A rare variety of cotton which produces fibers that change color depending on the angle at which light strikes them.

12598.name: Stalk of Ramie
12598.description: A variety of swift-growing grass native to the Near East. The stalks can be dried and processed into thin threads which, when spun together, can be woven into a cloth not unlike hemp.

12599.name: Chimera Mane
12599.description: The bristly mane of a biologically engineered monstrosity.

12600.name: Crawler Cocoon
12600.description: The sticky cocoon of a giant crawler.

12602.name: Enchanted Hardsilver Ink
12602.description: Ink fortified with hardsilver sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

12603.name: Enchanted Aurum Regis Ink
12603.description: Ink fortified with aurum regis sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

12604.name: Holy Water
12604.description: Water blessed by an anointed Halonic Orthodox priest. Used to exorcise most evil spirits from worldly items.

12605.name: Hallowed Water
12605.description: Water blessed by an anointed Halonic Orthodox priest. Used to exorcise evil spirits from worldly items.

12606.name: Astral Oil
12606.description: Refined oil with an unbalanced elemental aspect tipping towards astral.

12608.name: Growth Formula Zeta
12608.description: This alchemically formulated potation accelerates the growth of foliage.

12609.name: Bear Fat
12609.description: This musky all-purpose oil is commonly used in tinctures as well as lamps.

12610.name: Crystal Glass
12610.description: This exceptionally transparent glass does not actually contain any crystal, but earns its name for being as clear as crystallized aether.

12611.name: Black Firesand
12611.description: A higher concentration of saltpeter makes this flammable powder slightly more explosive than normal firesand.

12612.name: Grade 1 Strength Dissolvent
12612.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12613.name: Grade 1 Dexterity Dissolvent
12613.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12614.name: Grade 1 Vitality Dissolvent
12614.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12615.name: Grade 1 Intelligence Dissolvent
12615.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12616.name: Grade 1 Mind Dissolvent
12616.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12617.name: Grade 2 Strength Dissolvent
12617.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12618.name: Grade 2 Dexterity Dissolvent
12618.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12619.name: Grade 2 Vitality Dissolvent
12619.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

12627.name: Dragon Scale
12627.description: This rock-hard scale can withstand the blow of a Roegadyn-wielded battleaxe.

12628.name: Deepeye Tears
12628.description: It would take at least twenty tears shed from a heartbroken Lalafellin maiden to equal the liquid volume of one deepeye tear.

12629.name: Dhalmel Saliva
12629.description: The odor of dhalmel saliva has been likened to that of the bloated corpse of a blue cheese artisan drowned in a Grand Company camp latrine and left to sit in the hot sun for a sennight.

12630.name: Dragon Blood
12630.description: Most likely the blood of a dragon. For some unknown reason, the humours will not coagulate.

12631.name: Dravanian Spring Water
12631.description: Clear water taken from a spring in the foothills of Abalathia's Spine.

12632.name: Abalathian Spring Water
12632.description: Clear water taken from a spring on one of the many islets floating above Abalathia's Spine.

12633.name: Skyspring Water
12633.description: Crystal-clear water taken from a secluded spring located on a remote islet floating above the Sea of Clouds.

12634.name: Seventh Heaven
12634.description: A rare flower that has an elemental aspect tipped severely in the direction of astral.

12635.name: Gelato Flesh
12635.description: A quivering gelatinous lump of voidsent flesh neither cold nor sweet. Consumption is not recommended, even during times of starvation.

12636.name: Wyvern Wing
12636.description: The thick leathery wing of a wyvern.

12638.name: Coneflower
12638.description: Brought back from the New World in the west, this plant bearing large, horn-shaped flowers has been recently discovered to be effective in curing several different ailments.

12639.name: Cow Bitter
12639.description: This sweet-smelling perennial can be found growing in all of the Three Great Continents.

12640.name: Dandelion
12640.description: This common flower produces a globe of lightweight seeds that are carried remarkable distances when blown in the wind. While the stalk is filled with a toxic milky substance, the leaves and roots can be dried and brewed into medicinal infusions.

12641.name: Gaelicatnip
12641.description: A relative to pepper- and spearmint, gaelicatnip is an aromatic herb often brewed into teas. While it has no effect on the five races, the oil contained in the leaves is known to cause gaelicats and other normally aggressive feline beastkin to exhibit excessively playful behavior.

12642.name: Rue
12642.description: A low-growing shrub recognizable by its tiny yellow flowers and faint odor. The leaves contain a mild irritant that, when rubbed against the skin, may cause minor reddening and swelling.

12643.name: Coriander
12643.description: A highly fragrant herb. The leaves can be harvested and used in salads, or the plant can be allowed to bolt and the seeds gathered and used to spice ale.

12644.name: Aurum Regis Cylinder
12644.description: This small music box cylinder is studded with myriad pins arranged in a queer pattern. When placed in a music box and attached to the motor, the cylinder will rotate, causing the pins to strike the box's comb, creating music.

12657.name: Magnanimous Mogcrown
12657.description: A gaudy moogle-sized crown crafted by moogles for use during moogle celebrations.

12658.name: Dusk Leather
12658.description: An especially dark variety of leather often used in formalwear and uniforms.

12707.name: Bladed Steel Jig
12707.description: An all-purpose fishing lure crafted by combining three smaller lures.

12736.name: Blue Cloud Coral
12736.description:
A blue, lightweight coral found growing on the floating islands above Eorzea.

[Suitable for printing on medium canvases.]

fish.guide: This blue variety of cloud coral is harvested in great numbers by the Vanu tribes of Abalathia and ground into a fine blue powder. The powder is mixed with spring water and spores of the morrowmote to create a thick paste which is generously applied to the beaks of shamans before rituals.

12758.name: Mogpom
12758.description:
An algal sphere found collecting in the lone pool on the floating islet of Greensward.

[Suitable for printing on small canvases.]

fish.guide: A distant cousin to the lamp marimo, moogles will avoid mogpoms at all costs, believing them to be the discarded poms of their fallen comrades.

12877.name: Pearl Sprouts
12877.description: Tiny cabbage-like vegetables native to the highlands of Coerthas.

12878.name: Cyclops Onion
12878.description: A giant yellow onion often found growing on Abalathia's Spine.

12879.name: Emerald Beans
12879.description: A deep-green legume recently discovered growing on the floating islets above the Sea of Clouds.

12880.name: Highland Wheat
12880.description: A variety of dark-colored wheat suited to the rocky soil, shorter days, and colder temperatures of the Coerthas highlands.

12882.name: Coerthan Tea Leaves
12882.description: Considerably smaller than Thanalan tea leaves, more than double the amount of Ishgardian tea leaves are required to brew a single cup of tea.

12883.name: Mist Dill
12883.description: A fragrant herb characterized by its thin leaves. It is used in both medicines and culinary dishes.

12884.name: Chives
12884.description: A thin green onion used in many Ishgardian dishes.

12885.name: Magma Beet
12885.description: A sweet, easy-to-grow tuber native to Abalathia's Spine, these deep-red beets are a staple in Ishgardian culinary culture.

12887.name: Sesame Seeds
12887.description: A tiny seed rich in aromatic oil, sesame is native to Meracydia, and thought to have first been brought to Eorzea by migrating Miqo'te.

12889.name: Heavens Lemon
12889.description:
Possibly due to the increased sunlight it receives growing above the clouds, heavens lemons lack the acidity of normal sun lemons.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

12891.name: Birch Sap
12891.description: A thin clear sap harvested from birch trees.

12893.name: Dark Chestnut
12893.description: The spine-encased fruit of the dark chestnut tree.

12896.name: Old World Fig
12896.description:
A symbol of long life and femininity, this autumn fruit was originally brought from their homeland to Eorzea by the Sharlayans.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

12897.name: Cloud Banana
12897.description:
Though it resembles a tree, cloud bananas actually grow from an oversized herb. That does not, however, make them any less sweet.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

12898.name: Morel
12898.description: This rare mushroom with an oblong webbed cap is highly sought after by culinarians the realm over.

12899.name: Porcini
12899.description: A large fragrant mushroom popular in Coerthan cuisine.

12900.name: Chysahl Greens
12900.description: Though nearly identical in shape and color to gysahl greens, chysahl greens have a deeper, earthier flavor that chocobos (and man) seem to prefer.

12901.name: Abalathian Rock Salt
12901.description: Mined from veins found in Abalathia's Spine, this pinkish salt has a high mineral content which adds depth to its flavor.

12902.name: Honeydew Almonds
12902.description: A sweet variety of rare white almonds.

12903.name: Dravanian Paprika
12903.description: A rare pepper that is more sweet than it is spicy.

12904.name: Snurbleberry
12904.description:
This sweet, yet tart red berry is covered in tiny soft hairs that can be removed by lightly rubbing the fruit between one's palms.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

12912.name: Celestine
12912.description: A light-blue crystalline mineral which, when ground and added to any flammable material, will cause it to burn red.

12913.name: Garlond Steel
12913.description: A lightweight form of steel developed by the eponymous chief engineer of the Garlond Ironworks.

12931.name: Purified Coke
12931.description: A hot-burning fuel created by destructively distilling raw coal. This particular piece contains very few impurities, allowing for longer, hotter combustion.

12932.name: Raziqcoat
12932.description: Developed by a Near Eastern alchemist, this powder is used to treat and harden aurum regis.

12933.name: Dryad Sap
12933.description: A partially congealed ball of sticky sap extracted from a dryad.

12934.name: Moonbeam Silk
12934.description: A brilliant white silk spun by a rare breed of Eorzean spider.

12935.name: Odorless Animal Fat
12935.description: This gobbet of beastkin tissue does not exhibit the rancid odor most commonly associated with animal fat.

12937.name: Dawnborne Aethersand
12937.description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced matter. This fine sand emits a brilliant light discernible even at midday.

12938.name: Landborne Aethersand
12938.description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced mineral matter.

12939.name: Leafborne Aethersand
12939.description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced floral matter.

12940.name: Seaborne Aethersand
12940.description: The elementally aspected remnants of aetherially reduced sea life.

12941.name: Chalcocite
12941.description: A black metallic ore containing copper and traces of iron and saltpeter.

12942.name: Cuprite
12942.description: Though its appearance suggests it is a precious gem, this ore is actually a rare form of red translucent copper.

12943.name: Dravanian Mistletoe
12943.description: A variety of parasitic plant found growing on trees in the Churning Mists.

12944.name: Abalathian Mistletoe
12944.description: A variety of parasitic plant found growing on trees in the Sea of Clouds.

12945.name: Red Alumen
12945.description: A reddish variety of the mineral used by leatherworkers to tan animal hides. It lacks the deodorizing properties of its lighter counterpart.

12966.name: Bright Fire Rock
12966.description: An uncut, unpolished stone imbued with aetheric fire energy.

12967.name: Bright Lightning Rock
12967.description: An uncut, unpolished stone imbued with aetheric lightning energy.

12968.name: Granular Clay
12968.description: Crumbly balls of reddish clay added to soil to improve both moisture retention and drainage.

12969.name: Peat Moss
12969.description: Soil created by thousands of years of decaying flora gathering on the bottom of marshes.

12970.name: Black Soil
12970.description: This rich, dark soil receives its color from a high concentration of organic matter.

12971.name: Highland Oregano
12971.description: Due to its higher oil content, highland oregano is preferred over other breeds of oregano by apothecaries and perfumeries across Eorzea.

12972.name: Furymint
12972.description: Named after the spear-like shape of its leaves, this variety of mint has a cooler, less biting flavor than its darker-leaved cousin peppermint.

12973.name: Clary Sage
12973.description: A fragrant herb used in medicines, perfumes, and cooking.

12996.name: Chivalric Coat of Fending
12996.jobCategories: GLA MRD PLD WAR DRK GNB

13058.name: Coffin Lid
13058.description: Pried from the lid of a coffin, this plank of ancient wood is cold to the touch.

13060.name: Fiend Sap
13060.description: Left behind by the Fiend, this lump of sap appears to induce growth in living organisms.

13076.name: Mhachi Coffin
13076.description:
A faithful replica of a coffin discovered in the Void Ark.

※One per estate only.

13089.name: Sephirot Tree
13089.description:
An imposing objet d'art of a sacred tree.

※One per estate only.

13589.name: Adamantite Francesca
13589.description: A small throwing axe forged from adamantite.

13590.name: Pterodactyl Strap
13590.description: A thin leather strap cut from the cured hide of a pterodactyl.

13733.name: Pterodactyl
13733.description: A winged scalekin native to the Diadem.

13744.name: Wind Silk
13744.description: This silk is exposed to aetherial turbulence in order to strengthen its aspect to wind.

13745.name: Dinosaur Leather
13745.description: A large piece of cured dinosaur skin.

13748.name: Cloud Cloth
13748.description: Soft, light cotton woven from rare cloud cotton bolls.

13749.name: Pterodactyl Leather
13749.description: A large piece of cured pterodactyl skin.

13750.name: Sphalerite
13750.description: A semi-translucent mineral containing large amounts of zinc and iron.

13753.name: Cloud Cotton Boll
13753.description: The cloud-like flower of a cotton plant native to the Diadem.

13754.name: Blood Pepper
13754.description: A deep red variety of dragon pepper so hot it is widely believed by Far Eastern cultures to drive away malignant spirits.

13758.name: Cassia Block
13758.description: An expertly cut cube of fragrant cassia lumber.

13759.name: Tektite
13759.description: A type of naturally occurring glass first discovered after the Calamity which ushered in the Seventh Umbral Era.

13760.name: Eventide Jade
13760.description: A rare form of jade as red as a sunset.

13761.name: Fossilized Dragon Bone
13761.description: There is much debate amongst Eorzean scholars as to how much time must pass before a bone becomes fossilized. Some say a mere generation will suffice, citing evidence such as the proliferation of petrification magicks. Others believe it may take upwards of a thousand thousand years, casting doubts on the theories which state Hydaelyn was created a mere twenty thousand summers past.

13762.name: Periwinkle
13762.description: A mildly poisonous flower found across the Three Great Continents.

13763.name: Cloud Mushroom
13763.description: An aptly named fungus commonly found in the Sea of Clouds, wind providing a means of spore distribution from one islet to the next.

13764.name: Wind Widow
13764.description: A tiny poisonous spider that weaves sail-like webs used by the vilekin to traverse the Sea of Clouds.

13765.name: Old World Fig Seeds
13765.description: Old World fig seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

13767.name: Pearl Sprout Seeds
13767.description: Pearl sprout seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

13768.name: Coerthan Tea Seeds
13768.description: Coerthan tea seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

13842.name: Replica High Allagan Grimoire of Casting

13843.name: Replica High Allagan Grimoire of Healing

14003.name: Viltgance-type Hull
14003.description: A hull which utilizes a rigid, lightweight frame for a more stable flight.

14004.name: Viltgance-type Aetherwings
14004.description: The wings of a Viltgance-type airship, which adopt the same technology as Garlond Ironworks' manacutters in treating the wings with wind-aspected aether for buoyancy.

14005.name: Viltgance-type Forecastle
14005.description: The front half of a Viltgance-type airship, including the main deck and a sharp, narrow bow to balance air resistance.

14006.name: Viltgance-type Aftcastle
14006.description: The rear half of a Viltgance-type airship, with smaller aetherwings for supported buoyancy.

14048.name: Pudding Floor Lamp
14048.description: A slimy floor lamp designed in the likeness of a pudding.

14066.name: Faust Striking Dummy
14066.description:
A striking dummy created by the Illuminati to train their ranks for combat.

※Up to three dummies may be placed in a single estate, regardless of type.

14148.name: Lumythrite Ore
14148.description: An uncut, unpolished stone containing what appears to be lumythrite.

14149.name: Eikon Iron Ingot
14149.description: An ingot of smelted iron blessed by a primal.

14150.name: Eikon Metal
14150.description: A heavy piece of unidentifiable metal blessed by a primal.

14151.name: Smithsonite Ore
14151.description: This slightly lustrous ore is characterized by its extremely high zinc content.

14152.name: Eikon Cloth
14152.description: Finely woven cloth blessed by a primal.

14153.name: Eikon Fiber
14153.description: Tightly spun thread blessed by a primal.

14154.name: Frost Cotton Boll
14154.description: A soft and fluffy variety of cotton named for its resemblance to morning hoarfrost.

14155.name: Eikon Leather
14155.description: A large piece of cured beastkin skin blessed by a primal.

14156.name: Eikon Hide
14156.description: The skin of a large, yet unidentifiable creature, blessed by a primal.

14157.name: Treated Camphorwood Lumber
14157.description: A processed length of camphor lumber, treated with an alchemical agent to harden the wood.

14158.name: Camphorwood Lumber
14158.description: Processed camphor lumber. Its piquant aroma remains years after harvesting, making it a favorite for use in armoires and furnishings.

14159.name: Camphorwood Log
14159.description: A rough-cut log of camphorwood timber.

14160.name: Camphorwood Branch
14160.description: The thick branch of a camphorwood tree.

14161.name: Camphor
14161.description: The waxy, crystallized remnants of a liquid drawn from steamed bits of camphorwood.

14164.name: Gobcraft Resin
14164.description: A synthetic resin created by the goblins to protect leatherwork and carpentry from the elements.

14184.name: High Mythrite Nugget
14184.description: A small nugget of impure lumythrite.

14187.name: Griffin Leather Strap
14187.description: A thin leather strap cut from the cured hide of a griffin.

14188.name: Sewing Thread
14188.description: A spool of light, airy thread spun from frost cotton fibers.

14190.name: Beastkin Horn
14190.description: The mud-caked horn of an unidentifiable beast.

14743.jobCategories: THM ACN BLM SMN RDM BLU

14933.name: Tincalconite
14933.description: A pure white mineral closely related to borax.

14935.name: Galvanized Garlond Steel
14935.description: A lightweight form of steel developed by the eponymous chief engineer of the Garlond Ironworks. This particular sample has been treated to increase hardness.

14936.name: Faust Armor Plating
14936.description: A heavy square of body armor removed from the Illuminati-constructed battlemachina Faust.

14955.name: Lumythrite Sand
14955.description: Glowing sand consisting of tiny grains of lumythrite.

14956.name: Whitefrost Cotton Boll
14956.description: Despite their delicate appearance, the fibers of the whitefrost cotton flower are deceptively durable.

14957.name: Old-growth Camphorwood Log
14957.description: A glance at a cross section of this log reveals that a mere glance isn't enough to count the hundreds, perhaps thousands, of rings present.

15098.name: Allagan Aetherstone - Weaponry
15098.description: An Allagan device that, when affixed to a weapon, augments the weapon's strength.

15104.name: High Allagan Aetherstone - Weaponry
15104.description: An Allagan device that, when affixed to a weapon, greatly augments the weapon's strength.

15143.name: Staggered Shelf
15143.description: A bookshelf with crannies of various sizes, designed in the Doman fashion.

15152.name: Nidhogg Miniature
15152.description:
A statuette depicting the great wyrm, Nidhogg (Azure Dragoon not included).

※One per estate only.

15159.name: Large Garden Pond
15159.description: A large decorative outdoor pond encircled by mossy stones.

15160.name: Oriental Wood Bridge
15160.description: An arched bridge colored brilliant vermilion using traditional Far Eastern lacquering techniques.

15161.name: Oriental Deck
15161.description: A roofed, wooden deck with a Far Eastern aesthetic. Perfect for stoically fanning yourself on humid summer days.

15427.name: Horde Barding
15427.description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the great wyrm Nidhogg.

15567.name: The Law of Levin First Edition

15645.name: Luminous Fiber
15645.description: Glass fiber strengthened using alchemic components.

15646.name: Meteorite
15646.description: A glossy rock of sable black said to have fallen from the heavens.

15647.name: Crystallized Sap
15647.description: Tree sap that has crystallized and hardened into a small cluster.

15648.name: Light-kissed Aethersand
15648.description: Carefully selected granules of crystal. Despite being clear, when viewed under light, they shine a brilliant white.

15649.name: Glass Fiber
15649.description: Thinly spun glass remarkably resistant to high temperatures.

15653.name: Nidhogg's Scale
15653.description: A dragon scale pulsating with dark energies. Believed to have fallen from the great wyrm, Nidhogg.

15865.name: Firelight Seeds
15865.description: Firelight shrub seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

15866.name: Icelight Seeds
15866.description: Icelight shrub seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

15867.name: Windlight Seeds
15867.description: Windlight shrub seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

15868.name: Earthlight Seeds
15868.description: Earthlight shrub seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

15869.name: Levinlight Seeds
15869.description: Levinlight shrub seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

15870.name: Waterlight Seeds
15870.description: Waterlight shrub seeds suitable for garden cultivation.

15948.name: Lover's Laurel
15948.description: A highly fragrant variety of laurel named for the goddess of the moon, Menphina.

15949.name: Radiant Astral Moraine
15949.description: Luminous gravel with an unbalanced elemental aspect tipping towards astral.

15964.name: Sophia Miniature
15964.description:
A statuette depicting the Meracydian goddess, Sophia. (Barbelo statuette suspiciously missing.)

※One per estate only.

16013.name: Crystal Chandelier
16013.description: The aether contained within the crystals used to construct this magnificent lighting fixture emits an ethereal glow which enhances the mood of any hall or parlor.

16557.name: Sophic Barding
16557.description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble Sophia, the Goddess.

16706.name: Scintillant Ingot
16706.description: An ingot of smelted luminium ore.

16721.name: Star Cotton Boll
16721.description: A rare variety of cotton which produces nitid fibers that, when struck by light, coruscate like the very stars in the heavens.

16722.name: Brown Mushroom
16722.description: An earthen fungus that can commonly be found sprouting beneath trees growing in the Churning Mists.

16723.name: Noble Sage
16723.description: A fragrant herb used in medicines, perfumes, and cooking. Its deep blue flowers set it apart from its cousin, clary sage.

16724.name: Tungstite
16724.description: A bright-yellow mineral formed by the weathering of scheelite.

16725.name: Luminium Ore
16725.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the precious metal luminium.

16726.name: Zeolite Ore
16726.description: A porous silicate that adsorbs poisons, making it invaluable in myriad alchemical and medical concoctions.

16728.name: Scintillant Nugget
16728.description: A small nugget of impure luminium.

16733.name: Demicrystal
16733.description: Aetherial residue seeped forth from spiritbound weapons.

16897.name: Sophic Bead Fragment
16897.description: The radiant shard of a shattered bead that once bedecked the Meracydian goddess Sophia's holy raiment.

16908.name: Tempered Glass
16908.description: Glass treated in flame and then quickly cooled to increase its resistance to heat as well as its overall hardness.

17015.name: Scathach Miniature
17015.description:
A statuette depicting the high voidsent, Scathach. (Guaranteed to cast a shadow, even in complete darkness.)

※One per estate only.

17557.name: Dated Radz-at-Han Coin
17557.description: Currency once used on the Near Eastern island of Thavnair, now only sought by numismatists and historians.

17558.name: Ice Stalagmite
17558.description: Ice stalactites hold on tight to the ceiling of a cave. This is not an ice stalactite.

17559.name: Duskfall Moss
17559.description: Infusions made with this hardy brown-black foliage are believed to restore vigor.

17560.name: Glass Eye
17560.description: A small bead of naturally formed glass that could pass off as an eye, if viewed from thirty paces...in the fog.

17561.name: Rainbow Pigment
17561.description: Extracted from natural sources, this colorful powder can be prepared to create an equally colorful dye.

17573.name: Void Matter
17573.description: Little is known about this deceptively heavy substance save that its origins lie not in this world.

17574.name: Flannel
17574.description: Sturdy cloth woven with two varieties of thread─wool and cotton.

19850.name: Buckwheat Kernels
19850.description: A nutty grain that can be substituted for flour in breads and noodles. Found across the Three Great Continents, but grown in abundance in the heart of Gyr Abania.

19851.name: Loquat
19851.description:
A sweet yet slightly tangy fruit with a thin skin and a fleshy orange interior. Can be found in the warmer valleys of Gyr Abania.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

19852.name: Othardian Plum
19852.description:
A greenish pink plum common across the eastern continent of Othard.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

19853.name: Kudzu Root
19853.description: The root of the quick-growing kudzu vine is dug up and processed into kudzu powder which serves as a substitute for animal-based gelatins in Far Eastern desserts. It also is believed to exhibit healing properties, and can be found in most Hingan and Doman apothecaries.

19854.name: Doman Eggplant
19854.description: While just as brilliantly purple, this Far Eastern cousin of the wizard eggplant is noticeably thinner, and thus requires less time to cook.

19855.name: Daikon Radish
19855.description: The spicy daikon radishes of Othard are known to grow as long and thick as a grown Hyur's forearm.

19856.name: Sugar Beet
19856.description: These tubers can be several times sweeter than most fruit, and as such are commonly processed into sugar for sweetening cakes and other confections.

19857.name: Jhammel Ginger
19857.description: Jhammel ginger's bulbous, aromatic roots can be sliced fresh and added to stews and seafood dishes to remove gaminess, ground and steeped in hot water to cure head colds, or dried and ground into a powder to use as a spice for breads and cookies.

19858.name: Gyr Abanian Carrot
19858.description: Gyr Abanian carrots are not only longer, but a far deeper orange─nay, crimson─than those grown in central and western Eorzea.

19859.name: Green Leek
19859.description: Similar to green onions in flavor, the leeks of Gyr Abania are several times thicker, and far more piquant.

19860.name: Bamboo Shoot
19860.description: If removed from the ground when less than a fulm in length, bamboo shoots can be peeled and the fleshy interior eaten. A popular ingredient in Far Eastern stews and stir-fries.

19861.name: Mountain Popoto
19861.description: Crisp mountain popotoes contain high quantities of starch that create a viscous paste when the tubers are ground. This paste can be eaten raw, fried into cakes, or added to stews for thickening.

19862.name: Soybeans
19862.description: These emerald legumes grow two to three beans per pod on stout bushes that are ready for harvest in the early fall. The beans are most often pressed into the milk which is used to make tofu, or fermented into various savory pastes and sauces.

19863.name: Shiitake Mushroom
19863.description: These fungi native to the Far East are rarely eaten raw, the majority of those harvested dried, then used to make soup stock.

19864.name: Cumin Seeds
19864.description: A pungent spice that can be used in seed form, or ground into a powder, enhancing the aroma tenfold.

19865.name: Lotus Root
19865.description: Though they appear solid from the outside, the cylindrical root nodules of the lotus flower are riddled with holes, possibly to accommodate for the waterlogged environments in which the plant grows.

19866.name: Sun Cabbage
19866.description: The sweet, tightly packed leaves of Othardian sun cabbages are deceptively sweet, making them perfect in salads or stews.

19867.name: Fennel
19867.description: With an aroma similar to licorice, both the stalks and the seeds of this Othardian herb can be used to enhance the flavor of exotic Far Eastern dishes.

19868.name: Gyr Abanian Wheat
19868.description: A close cousin to highland wheat, Gyr Abanian wheat has been improved by Ala Mhigan farmers over generations to increase both flavor and yield.

19869.name: Persimmon
19869.description:
A hard, orange fruit common in eastern Othard. It is well known that seven summers must pass before a newly planted persimmon tree will bear fruit.

EXP Bonus: +3% Duration: 30m
(Duration can be extended to 60m by consuming multiple servings)

19870.name: Persimmon Leaf
19870.description: While not edible, the leaves of the persimmon tree are oft used in the preservation of other food.

19871.name: Gyr Abanian Mineral Water
19871.description: Clear water taken from a mountain spring on the eastern end of Abalathia's Spine.

19872.name: Crescent Spring Water
19872.description: Clear, odorless water taken from one of the many springs found on Othard's Fanged Crescent.

19879.name: Ama Nori
19879.description: This edible seaweed can be consumed raw, or dried into paper-like squares and wrapped around sticky rice.

19880.name: Ruby Tide Kelp
19880.description: A distant cousin of malm kelp, Ruby Tide kelp is harvested and dried in the sun to enhance flavor. Squares of the seaweed are cut and steeped in boiling water to create one of the savory broths used in Hingan cuisine.

19881.name: Gem Algae
19881.description: A variety of algae found in the Ruby Sea, commonly harvested for its salt.

19906.name: Beetle Glue
19906.description: An adhesive substance created by grinding down the chitinous carapaces of beetles and mixing it with heated pine resin.

19907.name: Ala Mhigan Salt Crystal
19907.description: These pinkish crystals grow naturally on the shores of Loch Seld.

19908.name: Pine Resin
19908.description: A sticky substance secreted by pine trees when their limbs are cut.

19909.name: Persimmon Tannin
19909.description: A translucent liquid extracted from persimmon wood by steeping it in hot water. Used in the tanning of raw animal hides.

19910.name: Gyr Abanian Alumen
19910.description: A brownish variety of the mineral used by leatherworkers to tan animal hides. It is only found in the mountains of Eastern Aldenard.

19911.name: Yanxian Parsley
19911.description: This Far Eastern perennial has a biting aroma that even many Othardians find off-putting.

19912.name: Alyssum
19912.description: This annual is coveted by perfumers for its honey-sweet aroma.

19913.name: Nagxian Cudweed
19913.description: Though recognized as a weed, this winter annual is edible and will oft be harvested in the late months for use in various Doman and Hingan dishes.

19914.name: Chickweed
19914.description: Though recognized as a weed, this winter annual is edible and will oft be harvested in the late months for use in various Doman and Hingan dishes.

19915.name: Nipplewort
19915.description: Named for the protruding buds from which its bright-yellow flowers bloom, nipplewort is a common winter annual whose leaves are gathered for use in Othardian cuisine.

19916.name: Windtea Leaves
19916.description: When steeped in boiling water, the leaves of this rare perennial change color, turning a bright bluish green.

19917.name: Holy Basil
19917.description: A herb with an aroma so heavenly, it will cleanse both your soul and your palate of ill flavors (or so say merchants who would see you buy their stock).

19918.name: Hallowed Basil
19918.description: A herb with an aroma so heavenly, the gods themselves must have blessed it (or so say merchants who would see you buy their stock).

19922.name: Moth Scales
19922.description: The powdery scales of a giant moth's wing.

19924.name: Rhino Beetle Carapace
19924.description: The thick chitinous head of a rhino beetle, complete with eyes, antennae, and mandibles.

19930.description: A rough-cut log of beech timber.

19931.description: A rough-cut log of larch timber.

19932.description: A rough-cut log of persimmon timber.

19933.description: A rough-cut log of zelkova timber.

19934.name: Torreya Log
19934.description: A rough-cut log of torreya timber.

19936.description: The thick branch of a beech tree.

19937.name: Torreya Branch
19937.description: The thick branch of a torreya tree.

19938.description: A small nugget of impure koppranickel.

19942.name: Durium Nugget
19942.description: A small nugget of impure durium.

19943.name: Oroshigane Ingot
19943.description: An ingot of Doman iron, smelted using Far Eastern techniques.

19946.name: Palladium Nugget
19946.description: A small nugget of impure palladium.

19950.description: Amber-colored sand consisting of tiny grains of koppranickel.

19951.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal koppranickel.

19952.name: Durium Sand
19952.description: Jade-colored sand consisting of tiny grains of durium.

19953.name: Doman Iron Ore
19953.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal Doman iron (also known as mochi iron for its resemblance to the Far Eastern rice cakes).

19954.name: Durium Ore
19954.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the metal durium.

19955.name: Doman Iron Sand
19955.description: Metallic sand consisting of tiny grains of Doman iron.

19956.name: Palladium Sand

20004.name: True Griffin Hide
20004.description: The downy hide of a true griffin.

20005.description: Forbidden in many markets for the nefarious means with which it is extracted, this wax is cherished by leatherworkers for the luster it brings to tanned hides when applied.

20012.name: Doman Yellow

20539.name: Wind-up Chimera
20539.description:
Crafted by piecing together the remnants of unsold automata.

Use item to acquire the wind-up chimera minion.
20539.tooltip:
That chimera must be
his latest prize.
   - Hildibrand
20539.specialactiondescription: Reduces action points of all enemies within range by 50% of the maximum value.

20780.name: Starcrack Sand
20780.description: A metallic sand which simpleminded smallfolk believe contains pieces of the very comet Rhalgr tore from the heavens.

20781.description: This oblong gold coin once saw heavy circulation throughout Hingashi and the eastern provinces of Othard.

20784.name: Yellow Kudzu Root
20784.description: This variety of kudzu not only exhibits the curative properties of its more common cousin, it has been observed growing almost twice as fast. It has also been observed withering and dying twice as fast.

21057.name: Wind-up Ravana
21057.description:
Low on low he stands, gazing up to see.

Use item to acquire the wind-up Ravana minion.
21057.tooltip:
O Lord Ravana! Master of the
Sacred Blades! Wrath of the
Colony! Conqueror of the World!
   - Gnath Priest
