27774.description: Sap harvested from the vampire vine─thankfully not the color of blood.

27775.name: Starch Glue
27775.description: An adhesive substance created by boiling down assorted plant matter.

27776.name: Extra Effervescent Water
27776.description: Naturally sparkling water bottled at the source. Do not shake before opening.

27777.name: Refined Natron
27777.description: A pure white powder with no trace of impurity. Used in alchemy as a deodorizer and leavening agent.

27779.name: Sweet Alyssum
27779.description: This plant that blooms with myriad tiny flowers smelling of honey.

27780.name: Fernleaf Lavender
27780.description: A fragrant herb with notched leaves.

27781.name: Enchanted Dimythrite Ink
27781.description: Ink fortified with dimythrite sand to improve aetherial conductivity.

27782.name: Underground Spring Water
27782.description: Clear, sweet water bottled at its subterranean source.

27783.name: Lime Basil
27783.description: A herb that smells strongly of citrus.

27784.name: Tiger Lily
27784.description: A variety of tall-growing lily, the bulbs of which can be used in various medicines.

27785.name: Light Gerbera
27785.description: A type of gerbera named for its bright white flowers.

27791.name: Grade 2 Strength Alkahest
27791.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to strength, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

27792.name: Grade 2 Dexterity Alkahest
27792.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to dexterity, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

27793.name: Grade 2 Vitality Alkahest
27793.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to vitality, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

27794.name: Grade 2 Intelligence Alkahest
27794.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to intelligence, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

27795.name: Grade 2 Mind Alkahest
27795.description: When applied to items such as battle gear, this experimental alchemical liquid will dissolve away minute amounts of aether aspected to elements detrimental to mind, and by doing so, better attune the item and its wearer to the remaining beneficial elements.

27796.name: Multifaceted Alchemic
27796.description: This alchemical concoction, created through collaborative efforts by the Mean's various facets, can be put to myriad uses─not all of them safe or recommended.

27798.name: Island Wolf Fang
27798.description: A sharp canine tooth that once belonged to an island wolf.

27801.name: Hard Mudstone
27801.description: A particularly dense stone comprised of layers of river silt compressed down over thousands of generations.

27802.name: Hard Mudstone Whetstone
27802.description: A hard stone for sharpening tools made of metal or...less hard stone.

27803.name: Volcanic Tuff
27803.description: Volcanic ash compacted by pressure and time into firm stone.

27804.name: Tuff Whetstone
27804.description: A volcanic stone used for sharpening tools.

27805.name: Gale Rock
27805.description: As the name suggests, this variety of stone is more strongly aspected than typical wind rock.

27806.name: Solarite
27806.description: A deceptively plain stone that, when cracked, momentarily erupts with bright light.

27807.name: Shade Quartz
27807.description: Several small pieces of dark unpolished quartz.

27808.name: White Clay
27808.description: Crumbly balls of white clay added to soil to improve both moisture retention and drainage.

27809.name: Sweet Marjoram
27809.description: A herb cultivated for both its medicinal uses and pleasant fragrance.

27810.name: Bog Sage
27810.description: The azure flowers of this plant brighten the landscape when in bloom, but its true value is in its leaves.

27813.name: Agedeep Aethersand
27813.description: The coarse-grained, elementally aspected remnants of highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter.

27814.name: Agewood Aethersand
27814.description: The coarse-grained, elementally aspected remnants of highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter.

27815.name: Ageflow Aethersand
27815.description: The coarse-grained, elementally aspected remnants of highly concentrated aetherially reduced mineral matter.

27816.name: White Oak Branch
27816.description: The thick branch of a white oak tree.

27817.name: Yellow Alumen
27817.description: A more colorful version of the typically white mineral used by leatherworkers to tan animal hides.

27818.name: Purple Carrot
27818.description: A dark purple root vegetable with a reddish stalk, differing somewhat in vitamin content from the orange carrot.

27819.name: Harcot
27819.description: A particularly fragrant variety of apricot.

27820.name: Frantoio
27820.description: This olive cultivar can be used to produce a large amount of high-quality cooking oil.

27821.name: Amber Cloves
27821.description: This sweet spice made from the dried floral buds is used both as flavoring and in essential oils.

27822.name: Russet Popoto
27822.description: An easy-to-peel variety of popoto with thin skin and a high starch content.

27823.name: Curly Parsley
27823.description: This fancifully frilly parsley has an unobtrusive flavor that makes it perfect for use in otherwise bland dishes or as a garnish.

27824.name: Garden Beet
27824.description: This common root vegetable doubles as a source of inexpensive sugar.

27825.name: Blood Tomato
27825.description: The slight acidity of this bright tomato is guaranteed to whet one's appetite, making it a longstanding favorite of tavern owners throughout Norvrandt.

27826.name: Royal Grapes
27826.description: The flavor of these cultivated grapes has been intensified using a special bacteria. Though unpleasant to eat whole, they are suitable for juicing and fermentation.

27827.name: Night Pepper
27827.description: A dark aromatic spice used in cooking as well as pickling.

27829.name: Creamtop Mushroom
27829.description: A bulbous white mushroom that grows wild in forests.

27830.name: Bomba Rice
27830.description: This short-grain rice is more absorbant than other varieties and does not clump together when cooked.

27831.name: Pixie Apple
27831.description: A powerfully sweet variety of apple.

27832.name: Upland Wheat
27832.description: This staple grain was grown at high elevation.

27833.name: Broad Beans
27833.description: These large, spring green beans are easy to cultivate, and have served as a staple food for millennia.

27834.name: Gianthive Chip
27834.description: A normal-sized piece of a massive hive created by a giant honey bee swarm.

27835.name: Lemonette
27835.description: A tiny lemon replete with sour juice.

27836.name: Peppermint
27836.description: This refreshing herb is suitable for use in cooking, essential oils, and tea.

27837.name: Coffee Beans
27837.description: Beans that, with some effort, will become grounds suitable for brewing fragrant coffee.

27952.name: Immaculate Wingblade
27952.description: A lethal-looking piece of one of the Lightwarden Innocence's wings.

27954.name: Coarse Saltpeter
27954.description: A translucent crystalline substance often used in making glass, firesand, and dyes.

27955.name: Crimson Firesand
27955.description: The use of coarse saltpeter makes this flammable powder slightly more volatile than normal firesand.

27968.name: Highland Spring Water
27968.description: Mineral-rich water bottled at its high-elevation source.

27974.name: Steer Hide
27974.description: A large piece of thick and durable steer hide.

27976.name: Fireglass Leather
27976.description: A piece of cured leather with a sheen so glossy it's nearly reflective.

27987.name: Innocence Barding
27987.description: A suit of chocobo armor designed to resemble the Lightwarden Innocence.

28172.name: Trader's Cottage Walls
28172.description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a trader's shop.

※Can only be used with cottages on small plots of land.

28173.name: Trader's House Walls
28173.description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a trader's shop.

※Can only be used with houses on medium plots of land.

28174.name: Trader's Mansion Walls
28174.description:
A set of four walls designed for those who wish to transform their estate into a trader's shop.

※Can only be used with mansions on large plots of land.

28199.name: Raven Coal
28199.description: Once the dense coal has been ground into powder and mixed with water, it can be used as a substitute for ink. Be sure to keep it away from white clothing, as the stains are a bugger to get out.

28200.name: Amh Araeng Seasonings
28200.description: This selection of rare varieties of salt and spices native to Amh Araeng can be used to add a dash of elegance and a pinch of class to even the most unappetizing of dishes.

28201.name: Clinquant Stones
28201.description: Every region of Norvrandt is, for some reason, blessed with an astonishing variety of glittering, shimmering, sparkling, and otherwise shiny stones. Il Mheg is no exception, as is amply demonstrated by these fine specimens.

28202.name: Airship Fitting Components
28202.description: In the hands of an artisan, these bits and pieces gathered from around Kholusia will eventually become the decorations used to adorn Eulmore's fleet of airships. In fact, it took another sort of artisan to even find them in the first place, having been forced to separate the proverbial wheat from the chaff in some of the island's most perilous locations.

28203.name: Kholusian Miscellany
28203.description: While not everything included in this assortment of locally sourced materials could be considered valuable, the various items combine to convey the very essence of Kholusia. This could, however, be attributed to the pungent oceanic odor they all seem to share.

28716.name: Sandalwood Sap
28716.description: A partially congealed ball of sticky sap extracted from a sandalwood tree.

28717.name: Beryllium Ore
28717.description: A decent-sized piece of rock containing the precious metal beryllium.

28768.name: Skybuilders' Hemp
28768.description: Though this hardy plant can grow almost anywhere, the snow-blasted precipices of Ishgard have so far proven too steep a challenge for it to overcome. This particular specimen was harvested in lower La Noscea, an environment far more conducive to plant life─or any sort of life, for that matter.

28770.name: Skybuilders' Rock Salt
28770.description: Although upper La Noscea seems rather a distant location from which to source something as simple as salt, the Ishgardians are nothing if not particular in their tastes.

28772.name: Skybuilders' Iron Sand
28772.description: The tradition of measuring powdered substances in units of “pinches” has been the cause of many arguments, largely due to differences in finger size between the various races. Folk in eastern Thanalan, where this sample was gathered, have been known to ask Lalafells to measure when selling, and Roegadyn when buying, for obvious reasons.

28773.name: Skybuilders' Flax
28773.description: It is a well known fact among botanists that the flax in the South Shroud is superior to every other kind, for reasons far too complicated and boring for anyone else to care about.

28774.name: Skybuilders' Spring Water
28774.description: Having only traveled the relatively short distance from the Coerthas central highlands to Ishgard, this spring water is still remarkably fresh, though the icy chill threatens to freeze it inside the bottle.

28776.name: Skybuilders' Straw
28776.description: Why the skybuilders would specify that their straw be brought from the Dravanian forelands is anyone's guess. Perhaps the smell helps their chocobos sleep more peacefully?

28779.name: Skybuilders' Tea Leaves
28779.description: The thought of happy skybuilders drinking delicious tea was the only motivation you needed as you risked life and limb gathering these leaves in the Sea of Clouds.

28783.name: Skybuilders' Adder
28783.description: Venomous snakes are something of a rarity in Ishgard, so the skybuilders have ordered that some be delivered from the Azim Steppe to help improve morale. Workers displaying a lack of enthusiasm will be given some time in “the pit” to rediscover their commitment to the cause.

28789.name: Skybuilders' Vine
28789.description: Quite why a particular type of vine that can only be found in the Azim Steppe is necessary to the skybuilders' plans has yet to be explained. Perhaps they are planning to surprise you with a work of surpassing genius? Or perhaps not.

28793.name: Skybuilders' Cotton Boll
28793.description: This cotton must be very special indeed for you to bring it all the way from Lakeland in the First. You can only hope that the skybuilders appreciate you going the extra malm. And traveling to another world.

28795.name: Skybuilders' Wheat
28795.description: Were the other contributors to hear that you traveled to Amh Araeng in the First simply to procure wheat, they would think you are just trying to show off.

28798.name: Skybuilders' Resin
28798.description: Thankfully, the resin appears to have suffered no ill effects during your return from the Rak'tika Greatwood, meaning that it is still a gelatinous blob with seemingly no practical application whatsoever.

28916.name: Skybuilders' Toad
28916.description: What is worse than being born a toad? Being born a toad and then carried against your wishes from your home in western Thanalan to icy Ishgard, where if you don't freeze to death, are likely to be chopped up and boiled in a pot. That is what is worse. Much worse, in fact.

29669.name: Oddly Specific Latex
29669.description: It is a relatively simple matter for a skilled botanist to collect latex from a specified plant in a specified vessel by specified means. Excruciating, yes, but simple.

29670.name: Oddly Specific Fossil Dust
29670.description: Whether naturalists would wholly approve of the Skysteel Manufactory's appropriation of microfossil-rich powder for industrial purposes is a matter probably best not raised in company of said naturalists, as to do so would likely bring about swift confiscation.

29671.name: Oddly Specific Obsidian
29671.description: It's all about the sheen. Apparently.

29672.name: Oddly Specific Mineral Sand
29672.description: If Nimie is to be believed, the precise mineral composition by grain is key in sand-related projects.

29674.name: Oddly Specific Amber
29674.description: A hunk of fossilized resin of very particular hue, clarity, and age.

29675.name: Oddly Specific Bauble
29675.description: Given the detailed nature of their request, one would think that the Skysteel engineers ought to have been able to come up with a more precise means of referring to this so-called “bauble.”

29676.name: Oddly Specific Dark Matter
29676.description: Darker (and more specific) than your average matter.

29677.name: Oddly Specific Striking Stone
29677.description: This curious sphere tends to set nearby tinder alight at but a touch, whether such an effect is desired or not.

29684.name: Fat Cat Wall Chronometer
29684.description: This convenient timekeeping device will always remind you when it is time to eat─unless, of course, it is time for your pets to eat, in which case you will be repeatedly reminded long before you have the chance to consult your timepiece.

29968.name: Fireheart Cobalt
29968.description: Seasoned miners will recognize this as a type of sulfide, its composition lending its surface a permanent sheen that makes it look like a glowing ember in the light.

29970.name: Purpure Shell Chip
29970.description: A shiny piece of Purpure carapace.

29972.name: Merbau Log
29972.description: A rough-cut log of merbau timber, bearing the wood's distinctive scent.

29974.name: Duskblooms
29974.description: A flowering plant with tiny purple blooms.

29978.name: Imperial Fern
29978.description: Presumably named by one of history's many oppressed lower classes, this fern's appellation cannot but refer to the pretentious way in which it curls.
